def.__text: the first letter of the Greek alphabet
alpha; the first letter of the Greek alphabet.
I prepare for a journey, depart
I prepare for a journey, depart.
I am blown with the wind

I am blown with the wind (referring to the gentler motions of the
                  air).
I live as a Jew (in religion, ceremonially).
I lay a case before, impart, communicate, relate

I lay (a case) before, impart, communicate, declare, relate (with a
                  view to consulting).
I throw away from, throw overboard
I throw away from, throw overboard.
I abstain from, keep myself away from.
I forget entirely, make to forget.
I lead away, seduce, depart, abstain from

I make to stand away, draw away, repel, take up a position away from,
                  withdraw from, leave, abstain from.

Amon (Amos), son of Manasseh and father of Josiah, an ancestor of
                  Jesus.
I make known to again, make to be recognized

I recognize; pass: I am made known, cause myself to be
                  recognized.
Bar-Jonas, son of Jonas, the surname of Simon Peter.

Barnabas, a Cypriote Jew, uncle of John Mark; his other name was
                  Joseph.
Eber, father of Peleg and son of Shelah.
I expose myself to danger, am reckless
I expose myself to danger; I am adventuresome, reckless.
intrans. tenses: I rise up against.
I make drunk; pass: I become drunk.
Esli, son of Naggai and father of Nahum.
Achim, son of Zadok and father of Eliud.

Ampliatus (Amplias), a male member of the church at Rome, probably of
                  the imperial household.
Boaz, son of Salmon and Rahab, husband of Ruth, father of Obed.
Zerah, son of Judah and Tamar.

Ananias, (a) husband of Sapphira, a member of the early church at
                  Jerusalem, (b) a member of the church at Damascus, (c) the high priest at
                  Jerusalem.
I postpone, defer, especially: I postpone the trial of.

it is necessary, inevitable; less frequently: it is a duty, what is
                  proper.

(lit: I saw through), I cut to the quick (with indignation and
                  envy).
Hamor, a man whose sons sold a field at Shechem to Jacob.
I chatter, am long-winded, utter empty words, stammer, repeat.

the township Appi Forum on the Appian Way, 43 Roman miles from Rome,
                  was named.
right opposite, off (nautical sense), over against.
I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert
I change for the worse, corrupt, pervert.
I push or thrust away, reject
I push (thrust) away, repulse, reject, refuse.

an enclitic, emphasizing particle: at least, indeed, really, but
                  generally too subtle to be represented in English.
Aretas IV, King of the Nabataeans.
on the opposite side or shore
on the opposite side or shore.

Gabbatha, a sort of paved square, on which the procurator had his
                  judgment seat.
Nathan, son of David, and an ancestor of Jesus.

I stretch forth, mid: I hanker after, long for, am eager for, aspire
                  to.

Augustus, a title conferred on the first Roman Emperor, C. Iulius
                  Octauianus, denoting sanctity (almost divinity).

mid. and pass: I make a compact (agreement) with (together), covenant
                  with, agree.
sober, not intoxicated (with wine), temperate, vigilant.
I demand of, ask for, beg earnestly for.
a receiving, a taking to one's self, acceptance.
a matricide, smiter of his mother.
the material of a building, a structure
the material of a building, a structure.
I enfold, entangle; pass: I am involved in.
I throw off or away, cast, hurl.
I lick off, lick clean, lick up.
lest in any way, lest perhaps
lest in any way, lest perhaps.

Bithynia, a Roman province, north-west of Asia Minor and south-west of
                  the Black Sea.

(Hebrew), gen. case of Joses (a) son of Eliezer, (b) son of Mary,
                  brother of Jesus, (c) surnamed Barnabas (also called Joseph).
I burst asunder with a loud noise
I burst asunder with a loud noise.
a mill-house, the place where grain was ground.
second-first, a word of uncertain meaning.

I save (rescue) through (some danger), bring safely to, escaped
                  to.

I sound out (forth) (referring either to the clearness or to the
                  loudness of the sound).
I report, bring a report, announce

I report (from one place to another), bring a report, announce,
                  declare.
that cannot be searched into, inscrutable
that cannot be searched into, inscrutable, unfathomable.

(lit: I become sour, I turn, of milk), I am good for nothing, render
                  useless; met: I become corrupt.
to act as proconsul, be a deputy
to act as proconsul, be a deputy.

Areopagus, or Mar's Hill, an open space on a hill in Athens where the
                  supreme court was held.

I fit, join; mid: (the middle indicating deep personal interest) I
                  espouse, betroth; mid: I take a wife, give in marriage.

(literary and Jewish), without any preference (undue favor, partiality)
                  for a person.
Belial, a demon, and in fact a name for Satan.
I wash off, mid: I wash away (my sins, in baptism).

I subject to regulations, decree; mid: I subject myself to regulations,
                  am decree-ridden.

Bar-Jesus, the name of the magician and false prophet at Paphos in
                  Cyprus; he is also called Elymas.
Eve, the first woman; wife of first man Adam.
I amaze; pass: I am amazed (almost terrified).
I drag, draw, pull, persuade, unsheathe.
I ask in marriage; pass: I am betrothed.
a prier into other men's affairs

one who meddles in things alien to his calling or in matters belonging
                  to others; factious.
I put into a genealogy, reckon my descent
I put into a genealogy, reckon my descent.
I am poorly clad; I am habitually wearing an under-garment only.

Alphaeus; apparently two persons, (a) father of Levi, and (b) father of
                  James.
Antipas, a Christian martyr of Pergamum.
one posted on the right hand, a spear-man
one posted on the right hand, a spear-man.
I separate from; mid: I part; pass: I am swept aside.
prop: I fasten to; I lay hold of, touch, know carnally.
I afflict with sores; pass: I am afflicted with sores.

the Roman Province Achaia, governed by a proconsul, and practically
                  conterminous with modern Greece before 1912.
I speak or say in opposition, I contradict
I speak or say in opposition, contradict (oppose, resist).
I search diligently, I examine carefully (minutely).
I choke, strangle; mid: I strangle or hang myself.
I wipe off, wipe clean; mid: I wipe myself off.
I fatten, thicken; pass. fig: I become stupid, dull, unfeeling.
pass: I die, wither (like the grass).
Emmaus, a village not far from Jerusalem.
an offering dedicated by a worshipper

an offering dedicated (hung up in a temple) by a worshipper; a gift or
                  offering consecrated to God.

I remind, admonish, am reminded, remind myself; pass: I remember,
                  recall.

Asa, son of Abijah and father of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah about 900
                  B.C. for 41 years.
Elmadam, father of Cosam, son of Er.
I warm; mid: I warm myself.
(Hebrew), Jared, son of Mahalalel and father of Enoch.
having three stories, the third story
having three stories; subst: the third story.
I give a vote with, assent to
I give a vote with, assent to.
(Hebrew), Cainan, one of the ancestors of Jesus.

a temple, either the whole building, or specifically the outer courts,
                  open to worshippers.

I rob; mid: I set apart for myself, appropriate for my own benefit,
                  purloin.
a young bird, nestling; a young one.

(lit: I turn out from); mid. and pass: I turn aside (from the right
                  road), wander, forsake, and with an object: I remove from myself, shun,
                  avoid.
I agitate or disturb in mind
I agitate or disturb in mind, trouble.
I burn, set on fire, suffer inflammation
I burn, set on fire, suffer inflammation.
I have means, am prosperous, enjoy plenty.
I assign by lot, allot, associate with, follow as a disciple.
antelope; Tabitha, a Christian woman at Joppa.
I preserve alive (lit: bring to birth), save.

(a) I make desolate, bring to desolation, destroy, waste, (b) of a
                  person: I strip, rob.

anything happily and successfully accomplished, a beneficial and worthy
                  deed.

(I keep some one in a tight place), I press upon, cramp,
                  restrain.
worship or service of an image
I set at naught, ignore, despise.
I hire out, mid: I hire, engage.
it is advantageous to, it profits.

Naphtali, son of Jacob, founder of a tribe which occupied
                  territory.
I puff up, make haughty; pass: I am puffed up, am haughty.

(lit: I glue one thing to another), I join (unite) closely, cleave
                  (to), follow as an adherent.

(denoting speech in progress), (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell,
                  (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

I bind together; pass: I am bound together with, as of prisoners in
                  chains.
I overlook, take no notice of, disregard.
Ahaz, son of Jotham and father of Hezekiah.
things which one possesses, goods, property, belongings.
I remain or continue together with
I remain or continue together with.
Assos, a port of Mysia, in the Roman province Asia.
I pretend, regard, make a show of.
I say previously, predict, proclaim, foretell.
belonging to bees, coming from bees.
a gift, offering, anything consecrated to God.

a Levite, properly a man of the tribe of Levi; hence: a priest's
                  assistant, an under priest, as the members of that tribe were charged with this
                  duty.
I remind, possibly: I remind again.

taverns; Three Taverns, the name of a village or town on the Appian
                  Way, about thirty-three miles from Rome.
Jotham, son of Uzziah and father of Ahaz.
I force forward, run (a ship) aground.
I strike with panic or shock; I amaze, astonish.
I disturb, agitate; pass: I am troubled, alarmed.

lit: I raise beyond, uplift; mid: I lift myself up, exalt myself, am
                  arrogant.
I invite, encourage along with others

I invite, encourage along with others; pass: I share in encouragement
                  with.
I root, fix by the root
I cause to take root; met: I plant, fix firmly, establish.
commander of the Roman emperor's body-guard
commander of the Roman emperor's body-guard.
I cool, pass: I grow cold.
(Hebrew) Methuselah, son of Enoch and father of Lamech.
one of a family, whether child or servant.
Sapphira, wife of Ananias, an early Christian.
I cauterize, burn with a hot iron; hence met: I sear.
one speaking with difficulty, a stammerer
one speaking with difficulty, a stammerer.

(refers probably to a careful observance of religious restrictions),
                  religious (probably in a limited sense), devout.

Eliakim, son of Abiud and father of Azor; son of Melea and father of
                  Jonam.
Tamar, mother of Perez and Zerah by Judah, son of Jacob.

Zerubbabel, son of Shealtiel (Salathiel) and father of Abiud and
                  Rhesa.
I am unstrung, become weak, fail

I loose, release, unloose (as a bow-string), relax, enfeeble; pass: I
                  am faint, grow weary.
belonging to the tribe of Levi; Levitical.
I use force, violence, suffer violence

(a) mid: I use force, force my way, come forward violently, (b) pass: I
                  am forcibly treated, suffer violence.

experience of evil, suffering, distress, affliction,
                  perseverance.
finally, from now on, henceforth, beyond that
finally, from now on, henceforth, beyond that.

Gethsemane, a small place between the brook Kidron and the Mount of
                  Olives near Jerusalem.
I rust; pass: I am rusted, tarnished.
I tear off, as of garments.
I burn, am purified by fire

pass: I burn, am set on fire, am inflamed; glow with heat, am purified
                  by fire.
I convince, establish, give assurance to; pass: I am assured of.
(of meat), sacrificed to an image (or an idol).
from all sides, from all parts.
I sink in the sea, am drowned
I sink in the sea, pass: I drown, am submerged.
(adj: paved with stone), a mosaic pavement.
most swiftly, most quickly, as quickly as possible.
I shave, shear, cut off the hair.
I glue, cleave, keep company with

(lit: I glue); hence: mid. and pass: I join myself closely, cleave,
                  adhere (to), I keep company (with), of friendly intercourse.
Reuben, eldest son of the patriarch Jacob and founder of a tribe.
Melchizedek, king and priest of Salem.
I acquire, earn, purchase, make my own, preserve alive.
Enoch, son of Jared and father of Methuselah.
I cause to prosper, have a happy journey

I cause to prosper, pass: I have a happy (successful) journey, hence: I
                  prosper.
I name, impose a name on
I name, impose a name on; pass: am named.
Jannes, a sorcerer at the court of the Pharaoh.
I hang out, mid: I hang upon.
I remember, call to mind, recall, mention.
the greatest, the most, very great.
I conceal, hide (by putting something around it).
I strengthen, confirm; pass: I grow strong, become strong.
with one's whole household or family
with one's whole household or family.
I toss to and fro, fan, blow.
Cos, an island in the Aegean Sea, south-west of Asia Minor.
Melea, one of the ancestors of Jesus.
I leave behind; pass: I am left behind, remain, survive.

(Hebrew), Levi, (a) an ancestor of Jesus, (b) another ancestor of
                  Jesus, (c) third son of Jacob, the patriarch, and founder of a tribe named after
                  him, (d) son of Alphaeus, and called Matthew, a revenue officer and one of the
                  twelve apostles of Jesus.
I nourish on, am educated in
I nourish (sustain) on, am educated in.
I pour out so that it overflows
I pour out so that it overflows.
I gather together, crowd upon, press around
I gather together, pass: I crowd upon (some one), press around.

Laodicea, a city in the Lycos valley in the Roman province Asia, near
                  Colossae and Hierapolis.
I cry out to or against
I cry out to or against.

(Aramaic), either: Our Lord hath come, or: Our Lord cometh (will come,
                  is at hand).
mid: I summon to myself, send for.
I grow at the same time
I grow at the same time.

Cauda, Clauda, an island twenty-three miles south of the western end of
                  Crete.

(Aramaic form), Jerusalem, the capital of Palestine: hence Judaism, and
                  allegorically, Christendom, the Christian Church.
Sharon, the maritime plain between Carmel and Joppa.
I break, break in pieces, crush, shatter.

Mark, who also had the Hebrew name John, son of Mary, nephew of
                  Barnabas, coadjutor of Barnabas, Paul, and Peter.
I become vain or foolish, am perverted.
I change; mid: I change my mind.
I provoke to anger, am full of angry passion
I provoke to anger; pass: I am wroth or very angry.
I fawn upon, flatter, beguile; pass: I am perturbed.
I make liquid; pass: I melt (away).
I destroy utterly, annihilate, exterminate, root out.
ten thousand; also used for a very large number, innumerable.
I sit down beside, set beside.
I am laid bare, laid open
I am laid bare, laid open.

(a) I ordain, lay down, give the sanction of law to, enact, (b) I base
                  legally, regulate, direct.
(lit: I bind under), mid: I put on my feet, pass: I am shod.
Jairus, a Jewish ruler of the synagogue.

I release on receipt of ransom; mid: I redeem, release by paying
                  ransom, liberate.
I rub, tickle, scratch; pass: I itch.
Ragau (or Reu), an ancestor of Jesus.

I torment, pain; mid. and pass: I am tormented, pained; I suffer acute
                  pain, physical or mental.

a divining spirit, Python, called after the Pythian serpent said to
                  have guarded the oracle at Delphi and been slain by Apollo.
service rendered only while the master watches
eye-service; service rendered only while the master watches.
I bring to the same form with, conform
I bring to the same form with, conform.
I initiate, instruct; pass: I am disciplined, learn (a lesson).
I am voted or classed with
I am voted or classed with.

trans: I hold before; mid: I excuse myself; intrans: I project, excel,
                  surpass, have preeminence.
I pour out as a libation
I pour out as a libation.

I glorify, acknowledge the glory belonging to, recognize as glorious;
                  pass: I am glorified in.
the inward parts; the heart, affections, seat of the feelings.
Moses; met: the books of Moses, the Pentateuch.

Lebbaeus, a pet-name for Thaddaeus, one of the twelve apostles of
                  Jesus; the full form of the name is not known.
Nineveh, a city on the Tigris in Assyria.
a tetrarch, ruler over a fourth part of a region.

properly: a division of the Roman army, numbering about 6,000 infantry
                  with additional cavalry; hence: a very large number; a legion.
I shine upon, give light to
I shine upon, give light to.
I wait upon, minister to, have charge of.
I am filthy; hence (morally): I am stained with sin.
I cause to appear, make visible.

I strengthen, render firm; imperative at the end of letters:
                  farewell.
Trogyllium, a promontory somewhat to the south of Ephesus.
I terrify, scare, strike with panic.
as far as, until, even to.
I arrange, take care, withdraw from

I set, arrange; mid: I provide for, take care, withdraw from, hold
                  aloof, avoid.
Rephan, the Saturn of later mythology.

Jannai, an ancestor of Jesus; Jannai was the son of Joseph, and father
                  of Melchi.

Rabbi, my master, teacher; a title of respect often applied to
                  Christ.

I eat, partake of food; met: I devour, consume (e.g. as rust does);
                  used only in fut. and 2nd aor. tenses.
I propose; mid: I propose to myself, purpose.
(Hebrew), Levi, son of Alphaeus, the publican.
I rule over as a tetrarch
I rule over as a tetrarch.
(a) I take to myself, (b) I take aside, (c) I welcome.

a collection, collecting (of money), particularly of an irregular local
                  contribution for religious purposes.
a bough, branch of a tree
a bough, branch of a tree.

Canaan, the whole of Palestine or Palestine west of the river
                  Jordan.
